&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;X @ P % T # M $ Y # J @ H&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; X is sister of P, P is brother of T, T is mother of M, M is husband of Y, Y is mother of J, J is sister of H.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;By using the symbols in the table given below, we can draw the following family tree:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/09/br%20testbook%20%281%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 243px; height: 356px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/09/F1_Madhuri_SSC_15.09.2022_D36.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 210px; height: 161px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As the gender of H is not known, H is either the son or daughter of M.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Son or daughter&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;<br><br>&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot;&gt;
